# Finance Ledger Reconciliation Automation

This is a finance ledger reconciliation automation project. It processes accounting
ledgers (organisation ledgers and party ledgers) and reconciles transactions between
the two sides.

The pipeline now spans the full flow: raw PDF extraction -> deterministic
formalization (with optional, token-limited AI layout profiling / failed-row repair /
unknown-label grouping) -> deterministic reconciliation and submission-quality
workbook generation. Reconciliation, matching, annexures, summaries, validation, and
all final balance/match decisions are owned by deterministic Python. AI is used ONLY
to normalize messy source input (layout, failed rows, unclassifiable labels) and never
makes a final reconciliation decision.

## Hard rules for AI / Cursor

- Deterministic Python owns reconciliation, matching, annexures, summary, validation,
  formula generation, and workbook writing. AI must never make final match decisions.
- Raw extraction and formalization must preserve the original source text and page
  references. Never drop, rewrite, or "clean" source text during extraction.
- Do NOT invent or infer missing ledger fields. If a value is absent in the source, leave
  it absent (empty), never fabricate it.
- Do NOT overwrite, mutate, or delete source files (PDFs, workbooks, original uploads).
- Do NOT print, log, or dump secrets (e.g. `.env` contents, API keys).
- Do NOT send financial documents to hosted / cloud AI services. All processing of
  financial documents stays on the local machine.

## Engineering preferences

- Prefer small, single-purpose scripts.
- Use type hints on functions.
- Use `pathlib.Path` for filesystem paths (Windows-compatible).
- Raise clear, actionable errors that name the offending path or condition.
- Produce audit-friendly output: preserve raw rows, record page numbers, methods used,
  timestamps, and per-page status so results can be traced back to the source.
